# ============================================================================
#                         LIA — .env.example
# ============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in CHANGE_ME_* values before first run.
# Generate secrets:
#   SECRET_KEY       → openssl rand -base64 32
#   FERNET_KEY       → python -c "from cryptography.fernet import Fernet; print(Fernet.generate_key().decode())"
#   Random strings   → openssl rand -hex 32
#
# LLM per-agent model/temperature/max_tokens are NOT configured here.
# They are managed via Admin > LLM Configuration (database-backed, hot-reloadable).
# See: docs/technical/LLM_CONFIG_ADMIN.md
#
# ============================================================================
# TABLE OF CONTENTS
# ============================================================================
#
# [01] ENVIRONMENT & LOGGING
# [02] SECURITY & AUTHENTICATION
# [03] DATABASE (PostgreSQL)
# [04] REDIS
# [05] API SERVER & CORS
# [06] WEB FRONTEND (Next.js)
# [07] SSL (Development only)
# [08] DOCKER SERVICES CREDENTIALS
# [09] HOST PORT OVERRIDES
# [10] OAUTH PROVIDERS (Google, Microsoft, Apple)
# [11] LLM PROVIDERS & API KEYS
# [12] LLM CACHING & COST TRACKING
